From: i915-rt-audit
Subject: [PATCH] irq_work: raise irq_workd to sched_set_fifo (FIFO 50)

On PREEMPT_RT all non-IRQ_WORK_HARD_IRQ irq_work runs in the per-CPU
irq_work/N kthread, set up with sched_set_fifo_low() = SCHED_FIFO 1.

i915 breadcrumb signaling (gt/intel_breadcrumbs.c, plain init_irq_work)
is therefore the consumer of every dma-fence signal on the system while
running BELOW the FIFO-50 i915 irq thread that produces its work, and
below any RT audio/userspace task (PipeWire data loops run FIFO 83-88
here). dma_fence waiters are not rtmutex-mediated, so priority
inheritance never boosts irq_workd. Under sustained RT load on the
IRQ-affinity CPU, fence signaling stalls unboundedly; with RT throttling
disabled (NSPA 0201) the CFS fallbacks (ksoftirqd tasklet leg, i915
heartbeat/retire kworkers) starve too, and the forced-threaded oneshot
i915 line compounds the collapse.

Raise irq_workd to sched_set_fifo() (FIFO 50), level with threaded irq
handlers, so deferred-from-hardirq work is not outranked by ordinary RT
userspace.

--- a/kernel/irq_work.c
+++ b/kernel/irq_work.c
@@ -308,7 +308,7 @@ static void run_irq_workd(unsigned int cpu)

 static void irq_workd_setup(unsigned int cpu)
 {
-	sched_set_fifo_low(current);
+	sched_set_fifo(current);
 }

 static struct smp_hotplug_thread irqwork_threads = {
